column5: What ever you all do,dont tell Glenn,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,        I WENT FISHING THIS MORNING  Yes it,s true,this is a fishing report.    Up before the sun,and headed for some perch,n.  Before I got to bussiness,I threw a party for myself    The oldest boy came down .He will never put that float rod away.He just loves it for all his fishing.      The action was pretty good for the first couple of hours,then died off.Fish seem to be in the deeper sections of the marina.Manage to get a feed for me mudder.      I must say,it sure was nice to get out there .Might just try it again.
GET OFF MY DOCK !!!  Any boats out Brian ?   TB
Just a tinbanger with an electric troller.

Hey, was he the guy we saw landing a fish with his float rod ice fishing on closing day?  We were between 6th and 7th Line Oro.  I snapped a pic of whoever it was.  Seemed an interesting technique that's for sure.    Joey
Nice mess of perch!! Man - you sure are early though - is that a Treestand in your truck???
And I thought I was crazy to try out my float rod for crappie this year
Yeah it is.I built that one myself. I use my truck for storage.LOL   The scariest thing of the day,was remember how to fillet them.
great report brian!  cleaning them? you didnt teach the young lad how to do that?
nice haul, thinking i may dump the ranger in either keswick or beaverton on sunday morning try to catch brekky
Bring it here,and I,ll help ya catch breky
oh, he does still fish  LOL
It was a great time out there bud.I almost thought about a shirtless shot,but it was still kinda nipplie.
I prefer to call it field dressing them. Joe Happy d-day bud

I see ya, I see ya!... na na na na boom boom!!!  He'll sit out in the woods in the freezing cold with snow up to his arse to shoot a wild dog... but has to have fair weather to fish!   Good on ya for getting out Bubba!!!   Did you have to borrow the rod and reel from someone?

Well Glenn,I have enough rods in the closet.I grabbed the nearest one,yes it was a bit dusty,and yes the line was coiled,but,it still caught fish.Makes one wonder about thin line and tiny baits eh?LOL  Knew it would make yer and my day.
